    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-15T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="56"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d56">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/1–1549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-15T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 15, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 15—2:16 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>68. With Communist occupation Tientsin rapidly being completed, question of
                    possible National air bombing of Tientsin is seriously disturbing Americans and
                    other foreign nationals as well as Chinese civilians in Tientsin. Such air
                    bombing of this city would at this juncture serve no military purpose and could
                    only be considered as inhuman act of a vindictive loser. Tientsin has suffered
                    grievously during past few days and for humanitarian reasons it is earnestly <pb
                        facs="0060" n="50" xml:id="pg_50"/> hoped that National authorities will
                    refrain, or be persuaded to refrain, from adding unnecessary sorrow to already
                    sorely tried city.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smyth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
